ngs three rarely translated works—Weevil (Curculio), Iran Man (Persa), and Towelheads (Poenulus)—to a wide contemporary audience. Richlin's erudite introduction sets these plays within the context of the long history of East-West conflict and illuminates the role played by comedy and performance in imperialism and colonialism. She has also provided detailed and wide-ranging contextual introductions to the individual plays, as well as extensive notes, which, together with these superb and provocative translations, will bring Plautus alive for a new generation of readers and actors.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aColoniesvDrama. 0aImperialismvDrama. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aamerican pop culture references.  aamerican references.  aancient comedy.  aancient rome.  aancient theater.  aannotated.  aanthology.  acolonialism.  acomedy plays.  acontemporary audiences.  acontextual introductions.  aeast west conflict.  aeastern culture.  aenglish translations.  ahistory of drama.  aimperialism.  amodern comedy.  amodernized translation.  aorientalism.  aplautus.  aplays.  apopular culture.  arole of comedy.  aroman playwright.  arome at war.  arome.  astreet lingo.  awartime audiences.  awestern culture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024274640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093822940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520938229423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520938229/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY